# Architecture Patterns

## Page Composition ‚Äî Decide Early, Change Never

Each role view is either a **single scrollable page** (sections composed vertically) or **separate routed pages** (shell key per page). Mixing these caused 3+ cascading rewrites in BM.

**BM final architecture:**
- `BM_MAIN_VIEWS = ["bm-dashboard", "bm-leads", "bm-todo"]` ‚Üí shared shell key `"bm-main"` (one scrollable page)
- `bm-meeting-prep`, `bm-leaderboard` ‚Üí own shell keys (separate page transitions)
- `bm-lead-detail`, `bm-task-detail` ‚Üí drill-down views with own shell keys

**When adding GM views, lock this down first:**
- Which GM views share a scroll page? (e.g., `gm-dashboard`, `gm-compliance`, `gm-cancelled-leads`)
- Which GM views are separate pages? (e.g., `gm-review-detail`, `gm-spot-check`)
- Update `GM_MAIN_VIEWS` in `InteractiveShell.jsx` accordingly

## Shell Key Rules (`getShellKey`)

- Views sharing a shell key share scroll position and don't remount on nav change
- Views with different shell keys get full AnimatePresence transitions
- **Never** add a view to `BM_MAIN_VIEWS` / `GM_MAIN_VIEWS` unless it's a section on the same scrollable page

## Section Map Must Match DOM Order

`BM_SECTION_MAP` / `GM_SECTION_MAP` in `InteractiveDashboard.jsx` maps view IDs to DOM section IDs. The key order in these maps **must** match the physical top-to-bottom DOM order ‚Äî `Object.keys()` iteration order determines scroll highlight priority.

## File Change Checklist for New Views

Adding a new view requires synchronized changes across:
1. `src/config/navigation.js` ‚Äî `roleNav`, `drillDownViews`, `roleDefaults`
2. `src/components/interactive/InteractiveShell.jsx` ‚Äî view‚Üícomponent map, `MAIN_VIEWS` arrays
3. `src/components/interactive/InteractiveDashboard.jsx` ‚Äî section map, section JSX, IntersectionObserver
4. `src/components/layout/Sidebar.jsx` ‚Äî nav items, chevron groups, scroll-into-view
5. `src/context/AppContext.jsx` ‚Äî only if new state/actions needed
